This paper is about conversational agents and their evaluation, which falls under the category of natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of metrics and evaluation strategies, which are common topics in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the subjectivity associated with evaluating conversations, which is a topic in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social computing (cs.SD).
